# UI Design Standards

All UI code must follow [docs/design/11-ui-tokens.md](../../docs/design/11-ui-tokens.md). Summary:

## Visual Hierarchy (MANDATORY - Clarity & Aesthetics)

- **Background layering**: Nested blocks MUST use different levels. `--bg-dark` (base) -> `--bg-panel` (panels/modals) -> `--bg-darker` (cards) -> `--bg-elevated` (floating blocks). Never stack same bg.
- **Label vs value**: In same block, labels use `--text-label`, values use `--text-value`. Do NOT mix.
- **Border hierarchy**: Main borders `--border`; inner splits `--border-dark`; soft splits `--border-dashed`; subtle `--border-subtle`.
- **Semantic colors first**: Gold/cost -> `--color-gold`. Exp/level -> `--color-exp`. Skill -> `--color-skill`. Victory/defeat -> `--color-victory`/`--color-defeat`. Use these instead of generic `--accent` when applicable.

## Colors (MANDATORY)

- **Never** hardcode `#hex`, `rgb()`, `rgba()` in components. Use CSS variables only.
- `var(--color-gold)`: **ONLY** for gold/currency/sell/costs. NOT for skill, victory, accent.
- Labels: `var(--text-label)`. Values: `var(--text-value)`. Muted: `var(--text-muted)`.
- Accent/selected/highlight: `var(--accent)`. Error: `var(--error)`. Warning: `var(--warning)`.
- Semantic: `--color-hp`, `--color-exp`, `--color-skill`, `--color-victory`, `--color-defeat`, etc.

## Fonts (MANDATORY)

- Use font scale tokens: `var(--font-xs)` through `var(--font-3xl)`.
- Avoid arbitrary sizes (0.72rem, 0.78rem). Use nearest token (e.g. `--font-sm` 0.75rem, `--font-base` 0.9rem).

## Backgrounds

- Base: `var(--bg-dark)`. Panel: `var(--bg-panel)`. Card: `var(--bg-darker)`. Elevated: `var(--bg-elevated)`.
- Hover: `var(--bg-hover)`. Selected: `var(--bg-selected)`.

## Tooltip

- Use `class="tooltip-wrap has-tip"` + `<span class="tooltip-text">`. No `title=` for user tips.

## Form Inputs (MANDATORY)

- **input / select / textarea / checkbox** MUST use game tokens: `var(--bg-dark)`, `var(--border)`, `var(--text)`.
- NEVER leave inputs with native browser defaults (white bg, system font, default checkbox/radio look, etc.).
- Focus: `border-color: var(--accent)`, `box-shadow: 0 0 6px var(--focus-glow)`.
- Match adjacent selects/buttons in font-size and padding.
- **Checkbox/radio**: Use `appearance: none` and custom styles (bg, border, accent when checked). Do NOT use native checkbox/radio appearance.

## Semantic Color Consistency (MANDATORY)

Same semantic content MUST use the same color token across all UI contexts. When adding or modifying UI, check existing usages and match them.

| Semantic content | Token | Contexts to keep consistent |
|------------------|-------|-----------------------------|
| Skill name | `--color-skill` + italic | Battle log, tactics panel, skill tooltip, skill choice modal |
| Basic attack (ć™®é€šć”»ĺ‡») | `--color-log-basic` | Battle log, tactics panel |
| Hero name | `classColor(hero.class)` | Hero card, detail modal |
| Hero class tag | `classColor(hero.class)` | Hero card, detail modal |
| Target hero name | `classColor(targetClass)` | Monster target display, battle log |
| Monster tier | `monsterTierColor(tier)` | Monster card, battle log |

Before adding a new place that shows skill names, hero names, or basic attack: search for existing usages and reuse the same token/helper.

## Prohibited

- `--color-green` (does not exist; use `--accent`).
- New color variables without adding to `style.css` and `11-ui-tokens.md`.
- Same background for nested blocks (causes flat, monotonous look).
- Different colors for the same semantic content in different panels (e.g. skill name in log vs tactics).
- **Native checkbox/radio appearance** (white box, system checkmark). Use `appearance: none` + game tokens.
